      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CANYA SCARLET (6) settled down midfield and held her position to the line when finishing 4th (28.95) at this track. Form here at the trip sound including three wins. Speedy beginner who can find the front despite the tricky draw. Has ability and can bounce back. FEDERAL CASH (1) has been a little hard to follow, finishing out of the placings latest but was in winning form two back scoring in a Grade 5 at this track. Safe beginner and drawn well on the inside. Has the ability and expected to do much better. PHOENIX SILVER (3) was strongly fancied last time over 380m at this track but in trouble and failed to finish. No luck latest and can bounce back. BEDWORTH (2) looks an each-way chance.",
